# ShipTracker Pro Environment Configuration

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (Optional - App works without these)
# =============================================================================
# The application works perfectly with local storage if these are not configured.
# Only set these up if you want to use Supabase for persistent data storage.

# Your Supabase project URL
# Get this from: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API → Project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Your Supabase anonymous/public key
# Get this from: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API → Project API keys → anon/public
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE VALUES (Replace with your actual credentials)
# =============================================================================
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImFiY2RlZmdoaWprbG1ub3AiLCJyb2xlIjoiYW5vbiIsImlhdCI6MTY0MjU0MjQwMCwiZXhwIjoxOTU4MTE4NDAwfQ.example-key-here

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the root directory
# 2. If using Supabase:
#    - Create account at https://supabase.com
#    - Create new project
#    - Get URL and anon key from Settings → API
#    - Replace the placeholder values above
# 3. If not using Supabase:
#    - Leave the values as placeholders
#    - App will use local storage automatically
# 4. Start development server: npm run dev

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - The app works 100% offline with local storage
# - Supabase is only needed for persistent, cross-device data
# - All features work without backend configuration
# - Data persists in browser local storage between sessions